## Identifiability of MDS Embeddings

* In the [**realizable setting**]{.ucsd-gold}, there exists a [**latent configuration**]{.ucsd-gold} $x_1, \dots, x_n \in \Rp$ such that $\del_{ij} = \|x_i - x_j\|^2$

* Let $\X \in \Rnp$ be the [**configuration matrix**]{.ucsd-gold}

* For any [**rigid transformation**]{.ucsd-gold} $g \in \euc$ (i.e., rotation + reflection + translation), [$\Del(X) \equiv \Del(g(X))$]{.ucsd-gold}



